MessageWaitingDataCoding

public MessageWaitingDataCoding(IndicationSense indicationSense,
                                IndicationType indicationType,
                                Alphabet alphabet)
                         throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Construct with specified indication sense, indication type and the alphabet.

Possible alphabet is Alphabet.ALPHA_DEFAULT, Alphabet.ALPHA_8_BIT & null, others will cause construction thrown an IllegalArgumentException. If the alphabet is set to null it means that the user message may discard.

Parameters:
indicationSense - is the indication sense.
indicationType - is the indication type.
alphabet -
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if alphabet is null or alphabet non one of Alphabet.ALPHA_DEFAULT and Alphabet.ALPHA_8_BIT.
